SliTaz Spk
================================================================================


The SliTaz Spk toolset provide tools and utils to handle SliTaz packages.


Spk
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Spk is the main tool to handle and play with SliTaz packages, it handle multiple
packages on cmdline and a wide range of --options wo will perform tasks such as
adding or removing packages using the toolset. Spk itself provide some small
commands such as ls or info.


Toolset
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Spk is separated in many small tools follwin the UNIX philosophy: one tool for
one task but do it well. Here is a list of proposal tools and ther functions:

	* spk-add    : Install local or online pkgs
	* spk-rm     : Remove packages: confirm in option ?
	* spk-up     : Upgrade the all system
	* spk-search : Search for packages or files
	* spk-...    : your turn Christina :-)


Devnotes
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	* packages.desc format: package | 1.0 | desc | category | website
	* packages.md5 format : de9f76250657000958ee0120d376613e  package-1.0.tazpkg
	* ...


Coding style
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Here are the spk coding style notes, follow them if you want your code included
in the package. These rules are in addition to cookutils coding style, please
read also cookutils/README


    * No bash, be Busybox Ash compatible
    * Use libtaz.sh, slitaz.conf and libpkg.sh
	* ...

================================================================================

